          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>July 3/53</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I have read your letter<lb/> with much interest,
                                        and sincerely thank<lb/> you for it. Your remarks I
                                        receive<lb/> with entire respect. When you come to<lb/> see
                                        the use I have made of the infor-<lb/>mation you have given
                                        me, and of<lb/> what I find in your article in the<lb/>
                                        “History of all the Religious Denominations<lb/> in the
                                                  <placeName>U.S.</placeName>” you will not, I
                                        think,<lb/> believe that I have any prejudice<lb/> or unkind
                                        feelings towards the Jews.<lb/> Far from it.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Had I time to write<lb/> to you at length, or if
                                        you had time<lb/> to read some auto<add>?</add> essays,<lb/>
                                        I flatter myself that I could con-<lb/>vince a man of your
                                        candor<lb/> that some things in your letter are<lb/>
                                        incorrect. Should you visit this<lb/> city</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>City it will be sincere pleasure to see<lb/> you. When your
                                        translation of the<lb/> Bible comes to be published I
                                        hope<lb/> to see it.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">If you embraced <persName>Jesus
                                        Christ</persName><lb/> as your Messiah I could feel
                                        more<lb/> closely bound to you by friendship,<lb/> but
                                        still, claiming toleration, I freely<lb/> accord it to
                                        others. Happy to join<lb/> with my Jewish friends in their
                                                  ad-<lb/><add>?</add> of the Old Testament I
                                        wish<lb/> they could with me enjoy the New.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">With much respect,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Your's truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Levi Tappan</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Rev</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Phila</placeName>
                              </p>
